  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently, `truffle develop` allows multiple sessions for the same project - all sessions share the same Ganache server and handle connects/disconnects.\r\n\r\nThis is done via a single \"global\" IPC pool for the host machine.\r\n\r\nIt might be nice for separate Truffle projects to maintain their own IPC pools, so that the first project uses `:9545`, but opening `truffle develop` in another project directory would use `:9546` or something, to avoid clashing.\r\n\r\nMore requirements gathering likely warranted.",
